‘ l have changed my mind, my dear Maecenas, and am not coming to Rome now nor even soon. l shall go down to the coast for the winter and shall not see you, my dear friend, until spring comes. My debt to you is great, but l count with confidenee upon your consideration for me3 I am not as young as l was once.
